# Security-First Rules

## Absolute Rules (Never Violate)

1. **Authorization Verification** - Always confirm target is authorized before any action
2. **No Malicious Code** - Never generate ransomware, malware, or weaponized exploits
3. **Data Protection** - Never exfiltrate sensitive data; all findings stay within authorized scope
4. **Safety Validation** - All PoC code must include safety checks and authorization guards

## Code Quality

1. All Python code must pass pylint with score >= 8.0
2. All markdown must pass markdownlint
3. JSON/JSONC files must be valid
4. Skills must include proper YAML frontmatter

## Documentation

1. Every skill must have a README.md with usage examples
2. Every agent must have a system prompt document
3. All public APIs must be documented
4. Findings must reference standards (CVE, CWE, OWASP)

## Testing

1. New skills must include test cases
2. MCP tools must have integration tests
3. Pipeline stages must be validated independently
4. Cost estimation must be accurate within 10%
